org.alljoyn.bus

Class Variant

  • Object
    • Variant

  • public class Variant
extends Object
    A DBus/AllJoyn datatype whose type information is encoded into the value field.

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      Variant(T value)
      Creates a Variant that represents a specific AllJoyn data type and value.
      Variant(T value, String signature)
      Creates a Variant with an explicit signature that represents a specific AllJoyn data type and instance value.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Variant

        public Variant(T value)
        Creates a Variant that represents a specific AllJoyn data type and value. This constructor is typically used by message senders (method calls and signal emitters) when a specific Variant type and value are known at the time the Variant is created.
        Parameters:
        value - object wrapped inside this Variant

      • Variant

        public Variant(T value,
       String signature)
        Creates a Variant with an explicit signature that represents a specific AllJoyn data type and instance value. This constructor is typically used by message senders (method calls and signal emitters) when a specific Variant type and value are known at the time the Variant is created.
        Parameters:
        value - object wrapped inside the Variant
        signature - the DBus signature of value
